RT by @OpenRightsGroup: The UK is introducing a digital reform bill that will scrap mandatory consent for cookies. 

@OpenRightsGroup says the proposal would make spying on people’s activities the “default option”.

@DanMilmo reports: https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2022/jun/17/uk-plan-to-scrap-cookie-consent-boxes-will-make-it-easier-to-spy-on-web-users
